Female. Colour and pattern of carapace, abdomen and legs as in male, patterning more distinct than in male (
Fig. 4 B, I, J
); calamistrum more prominent than in male; tarsi scopulate with two primary toothed tarsal claws and a single small claw lacking denticles as in male. Carapace pyriform in shape as in male; thoracic groove as in male; eyes as in male.

Distribution. Central America . The localities in northern Honduras , southern Nicaragua and central Panama (
Fig. 1
) represent new records.
